'''Settimo Vittone''' is a ''[[comune]]'' (municipality) in the [[Province of Turin]] in the [[Italy|Italian]] region [[Piedmont]], located about 50&nbsp;km north of [[Turin]], in the [[Canavese]] traditional region.

==Main sights==
The main attraction are the ''[[pieve]]'' (pleban church) and the baptistery of St. John the Baptist, most likely dating to the late 9th century. It is one of the main examples of pre-[[romanesque architecture|Romanesque]] architecture in Piedmont. Instead in Romanesque are the bell tower and the rectangular apse. It is home to numerous frescoes, dating from the 13th to the late 15th centuries.

